    Originally posted by Olav Bergesen View Post

    Jk-ide v2.4.8.6 Win11 64bit.

    Just downloaded the program. Two dll's is missing(MSVCR100.dll and MSVCP100.dll). After having copied them from elsewhere on the disk to the Windows catalog; I got, during load, an error saying something like(in english) "The program could'nt start correctly(0xc000007b). Press OK to close the program"
    Read the ReadMe.txt file and then follow the instructions to "Please read at least the "Installation" and "First Run" topics in JK-IDE.chm"

    "It uses a special build (compiled with VC10) of Scintilla as editing component. It has a new lexer and other additional code for Scintilla, therefore only scilexer.dll in this package will work properly (other scintilla builds dont!). Be sure to have the VC10 runtimes installed, search for "vc 10 runtime X86 download", Microsoft offers a free download package. The VC 10 runtimes are not part of the IDEs installation package, you must download and install them, if the IDE complains about missing dlls.
    "
    You need to instal the 32bit Visual C++ Runtime .
